 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-TYPE-002: Value::Ref admits unvalidated reference cycles. PROBLEM: Value::Ref(EntityId) allows any EntityId as a reference target including entities that do not exist in the store. Schema validation (validate_datom) checks value types but does not verify referential integrity at transact time. No mechanism exists to detect permanently dangling references. JUSTIFICATION: This is intentional for eventual consistency — C4 (CRDT merge by set union) means references may precede referents in a multi-agent scenario. The design correctly separates write-time flexibility from read-time verification. However, the absence of any diagnostic for permanently dangling references violates the completeness principle: every data quality concern should have a detection mechanism. SOLUTION: Add store.dangling_refs() -> Vec<(EntityId, Attribute, EntityId)> as a diagnostic function exposed via 'braid verify --refs'. No transact-time enforcement needed — this respects C4 while closing the observability gap. VERIFICATION: Returns empty for self-consistent stores; non-empty for stores with orphan refs. DEPENDENCIES: Independent of other findings. Low priority — complements F-SPEC-001 (verification completeness). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/datom.rs:52-85, crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs. SEVERITY: Medium. WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 2h."
